description: You don't need to go camping to learn how to make delicious damper bread. Try this damper recipe, with a tasty cheese and zucchini twist, at home today.

name: Zucchini Damper Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 140g salted butter, chopped (save 40g softened butter, to serve)
.80 cup milk, save 1 tbs to brush

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Line a large baking tray with baking paper.
Place flour, butter and parmesan in a large bowl. Using fingertips, rub ingredients together until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Season.

Add zucchini and toss to combine. Add milk and, using a flat-bladed knife, stir until mixture comes together. Turn mixture onto a floured surface and knead lightly until a dough forms. Shape dough into a ball. Transfer to tray and flatten slightly to form a 20cm round. Score dough into 8 wedges with a small, sharp knife and brush with milk.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden and sounds hollow when tapped. Serve with softened butter and golden syrup.
